sql:
SELECT AVG(holds_count) AS average_holds_per_desk
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(hold_id) AS holds_count
  FROM holds
  GROUP BY desk_id
);

SELECT COUNT(desk_id) AS total_active_desks
FROM circulation_desks
WHERE active_ind = 'Y';

external_knowledge:
- "On-time returns" are instances where materials were returned on or before the due date;
- "Late returns" are instances where materials were returned after the due date;
- "Total checkouts" is the sum of all times a material has been checked out;
- "Total holds" is the sum of all times a material has been placed on hold;
- The "on-time return rate" is calculated as the ratio of on-time returns to total checkouts, expressed as a percentage.

sql:
SELECT hold_id, patron_id, material_id, hold_date, expiry_date
FROM holds
WHERE status = 'pending' AND (julianday(expiry_date) - julianday('now')) <= 7;

SELECT desk_id, desk_code, desk_public_name, staff_name, hold_days
FROM circulation_desks
WHERE active_ind = 'true';

SELECT staff_name
FROM circulation_desks
WHERE hold_days = (
    SELECT MAX(hold_days)
    FROM circulation_desks
);

external_knowledge:
- "resource-rich" refers to the number of materials available in the library branches;
- "most abundant" indicates the highest count of materials;
- "listed from the most to the least" means the results are sorted in descending order by the number of materials.

- "hold pickup time" refers to the time difference between when a hold is placed and when it is picked up;
- "longest average hold pickup times" indicates that the query is looking for desks where, on average, holds take the most time to be picked up;
- "circulation desks" are the places in the library where patrons can place holds and pick up items.

- "burden of book holds" refers to the total number of holds placed at each circulation desk;
- "wealth of materials" refers to the total number of materials available at each library branch;
- "frequency of notifications" refers to the total number of notifications sent to patrons at each library branch.

- "library branch" refers to a specific location where library services are provided;
- "materials" can include books, magazines, DVDs, and other items that can be borrowed from the library;
- "circulation desks" are the points in the library where materials are checked out and returned.

sql:
SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN h.status = 'picked up' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(h.hold_id)) AS overall_pickup_rate
FROM holds h;

external_knowledge:
- "Circulation desk" refers to a library service point where patrons can check out and return materials;
- "Unique materials" refer to distinct items in the library's collection;
- "Top material" is the most frequently checked-out item;
- "Top patron" is the library user with the highest number of checkouts.

- Active desks are those with `active_ind` set to 'Y';
- `pickup_location_ind` indicates whether a desk supports book pickups;
- A desk that supports book pickups can be metaphorically referred to as a "beacon for book pickups";
- A desk that does not support book pickups can be metaphorically referred to as a "quiet corner for reading".

- "Materials" refer to books, magazines, and other items available for borrowing;
- "Holds" represent requests by patrons to reserve materials;
- "Checkouts" are the instances of patrons borrowing materials;
- The query helps in understanding the utilization and demand at each branch compared to the overall library system.
